HEADWORD: Terrorize
<hw>Ter"ror*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>terroriser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To impress with terror; to coerce by
intimidation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Humiliated by the tyranny of foreign despotism, and
<qex>terrorized</qex> by ecclesiastical authority.</q> <rj><qau>J. A.
Symonds.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Terrorless</ent>⟦br⟧
